OCaml 5.x headers use C11 atomic builtins (atomic_load_acquire,
atomic_store_release) as compiler builtins without a declaration in C99 mode.
Suppress the implicit-function-declaration diagnostic so the builtins are
accepted; they resolve at link time via the compiler runtime.

--- a/src/dune
+++ b/src/dune
@@ -6,6 +6,7 @@
  (foreign_stubs
   (language c)
   (names mlmpfr_stubs)
-  (flags
-   (:include c_flags.sexp)))
+  (flags
+   (:include c_flags.sexp)
+   -Wno-implicit-function-declaration))
  (c_library_flags
